1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,980
[2025 Chungnam location incentive
production support project]

2
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:13,500
[Woo Jihan]

3
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:18,340
[Shin Jeongyou]

4
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,600
[Min Dohee]

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,680
[Seo Seunghyeon]

6
00:00:30,420 --> 00:00:35,020
[Always Meet Again]

7
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,560
Is the light bulb faulty?

8
00:00:59,580 --> 00:01:00,200
Hey!

9
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:36,680
What were you thinking!

10
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,870
What if you got hurt?

11
00:01:39,050 --> 00:01:39,740
Huh?

12
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,300
The light bulb seemed faulty.

13
00:01:46,650 --> 00:01:47,590
It looks fine.

14
00:01:48,210 --> 00:01:49,090
I know...

15
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,270
Hey, Taejun, wait.

16
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,229
Hear me out first.

17
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:57,650
You'll fight with him at school
in two days.

18
00:01:58,430 --> 00:01:59,640
Two days later,

19
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:01,870
he'll get hurt
while changing a light bulb.

20
00:02:01,870 --> 00:02:02,890
The location's changed,

21
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:04,290
so why is this happening？

22
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,380
What did you say?

23
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:08,710
No, nothing.

24
00:02:13,390 --> 00:02:16,600
[Episode 7:
What's Our End?]

25
00:02:20,260 --> 00:02:21,260
Really?

26
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:22,950
Gosh, that was close.

27
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,400
Luckily he didn't get hurt.

28
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:30,370
That's a relief.

29
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:33,920
But why'd it happen at your house?

30
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:35,040
I know, right?

31
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:40,600
By the way,

32
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,200
I've been wanting to ask you something.

33
00:02:43,420 --> 00:02:44,940
How'd you know

34
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,460
something would happen

35
00:02:48,470 --> 00:02:49,470
to Woojin?

36
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,090
It's not that I don't trust you.

37
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:57,170
But logically...

38
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,500
I believe you from the bottom of my heart.

39
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:03,840
But to be honest, logically,
it's hard to understand,

40
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,630
isn't it?

41
00:03:07,350 --> 00:03:08,050
Right?

42
00:03:08,870 --> 00:03:09,870
What's going on?

43
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:14,990
I'll tell you...

44
00:03:15,670 --> 00:03:17,270
I'll tell you when it's over.

45
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:19,550
When it's over?

46
00:03:19,890 --> 00:03:20,460
What?

47
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:21,590
What's over?

48
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:25,640
After Woojin gets through the week.

49
00:03:27,820 --> 00:03:28,670
O-Oh...

50
00:03:28,820 --> 00:03:29,340
OK.

51
00:03:30,770 --> 00:03:31,700
Jang Hyeseong.

52
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:36,530
What secrets are you two whispering about?

53
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,030
Huh?

54
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:41,940
What secrets? No way.

55
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,160
Nothing of that sort.

56
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:45,220
Yeah... You're here.

57
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:48,100
I'll leave you two to finish the mural.

58
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:48,900
I'm off.

59
00:03:49,510 --> 00:03:50,560
Oh, OK. Bye.

60
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,630
-Good luck with the mural.
-Thanks.

61
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,640
The old Park Taejun is back.

62
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,440
Yeah.

63
00:03:57,650 --> 00:03:58,570
Oh, um...

64
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:03,170
Do you want to go on a trip?

65
00:04:04,290 --> 00:04:04,870
Hmm?

66
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,530
I mean, the vacation is short.

67
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:09,870
Let's go on an overnight trip
at someplace fun

68
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:11,200
and have some good food.

69
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:12,220
Woah...

70
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,630
I'd love that.

71
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,399
Let's bike there.

72
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,240
Uh...

73
00:04:19,589 --> 00:04:21,430
Biking's a bit dangerous.

74
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:22,570
Hey.

75
00:04:22,940 --> 00:04:24,390
What's dangerous about biking?

76
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:25,720
We'll just be careful.

77
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:29,630
I'm so excited.

78
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:33,340
Then,

79
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,020
you must be really careful.

80
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,230
Of course.

81
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:50,380
You're here.

82
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,840
What took you so long?

83
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:54,250
My bike was locked up by someone.

84
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:57,760
L-Locked up?

85
00:04:58,470 --> 00:05:00,470
Wait till I get my hands on who did it.

86
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:03,400
Let's go.

87
00:05:03,590 --> 00:05:04,310
Hey.

88
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:06,810
You must be super careful.

89
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,650
Don't mess around or anything.

90
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:09,800
Are you my mom?

91
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,060
What's with all this nagging?

92
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,340
Hey, I'm a great biker.

93
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,060
Just be careful yourself.

94
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,440
Let's go.

95
00:05:21,230 --> 00:05:23,610
Please let us get through today safely.

96
00:06:04,810 --> 00:06:06,230
Ah! This is nice!

97
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:12,330
Hey.

98
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,800
Look over there.

99
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,520
It's totally submerged.

100
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,390
Someone should be living there too.

101
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:19,290
There's no way someone lives there.

102
00:06:19,290 --> 00:06:20,020
Hmm?

103
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,800
Hey!

104
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:24,450
Ho!

105
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:31,020
You've got ice cream all over your face.

106
00:07:57,930 --> 00:07:58,930
I had...

107
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:01,680
a great time today.

108
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,100
Yeah.

109
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,180
Me too.

110
00:08:15,010 --> 00:08:16,010
Hyeseong.

111
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,360
Hmm?

112
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:21,090
I had so much fun today.

113
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,400
I'll never forget this trip.

114
00:10:25,510 --> 00:10:26,510
Me too.

115
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:28,420
Let's come again.

116
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,800
Can we?

117
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:35,580
Why not?

118
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,160
We can just come if we want.

119
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:39,740
Yeah.

120
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:43,240
I hope we can come again.

121
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:45,920
Hmm?

122
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,710
If I can stop your death...

123
00:10:49,990 --> 00:10:51,250
If I stop your death...

124
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:53,550
I won't

125
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,940
leave you behind again.

126
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:57,090
But

127
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,730
if I can't stop it...

128
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,200
I'm leaving soon.

129
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:05,300
What?

130
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:07,380
Where are you going?

131
00:11:13,050 --> 00:11:14,050
To study abroad.

132
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:15,910
What?

133
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:18,510
All of a sudden?

134
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:24,020
You know

135
00:11:24,730 --> 00:11:26,620
my dream is to be an artist.

136
00:11:28,290 --> 00:11:30,090
I'm leaving to fulfill my dream.

137
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,650
But it's so sudden.

138
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:36,570
I should have told you earlier.

139
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:38,970
Sorry.

140
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:50,950
Is this trip just

141
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,990
to make your last memories with me

142
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,340
before you leave?

143
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,480
No, it's not like that.

144
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:07,500
When are you leaving?

145
00:12:16,410 --> 00:12:17,410
Soon.

146
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:19,270
What?

147
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,440
I'll tell you

148
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,720
when it's decided.

149
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,550
Are you really leaving?

150
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:08,440
You're really leaving?

151
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,140
So this is really to commemorate our end.

152
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,960
It's not that.

153
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:35,470
Then why are you...

154
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,910
leaving all of a sudden?

155
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,720
If I can change your fate,

156
00:13:47,190 --> 00:13:48,190
we will

157
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:50,600
definitely meet again.

158
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:54,120
Don't answer if you don't want to.

159
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,100
We...

160
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:02,610
must meet again.

161
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,810
Will you come back?

162
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:20,490
If you're still alive.

163
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:25,170
What do you mean?

164
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:34,440
No, I mean...

165
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,110
If I live

166
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:46,190
a good life there

167
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:49,780
and you live your life well here,

168
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:57,130
won't we get to meet again?

169
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,400
Lee Woojin!

170
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:16,940
Where did he go now?

171
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:22,500
Lee Woojin!

172
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:31,340
Hey.

173
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,550
Where were you?

174
00:16:34,310 --> 00:16:35,620
Just to buy breakfast.

175
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,470
How could you disappear
without telling me?

176
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:39,470
I was so worried!

177
00:16:40,890 --> 00:16:42,690
You were sleeping so well, so...

178
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,220
Hey, I'm not a kid.

179
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:47,180
No, I...

180
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,930
Why are you so worried about me?

181
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:51,620
If you're so worried,

182
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,180
why are you leaving me so suddenly?

183
00:16:58,180 --> 00:16:58,940
Hey.

184
00:17:00,970 --> 00:17:02,190
No, I just...

185
00:17:02,570 --> 00:17:04,300
I don't want you to be in danger.

186
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:06,160
Fine.

187
00:17:06,819 --> 00:17:08,150
Thanks for the concern.

188
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:09,940
You must be hungry.

189
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:11,010
Let's eat.

190
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:26,319
Before you leave,

191
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:29,150
we'll finish the mural, right?

192
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:30,740
Hmm?

193
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:33,340
Since you're going abroad.

194
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:36,150
Yeah.

195
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:38,770
We said we'd finish it together.

196
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:42,310
I was planning to finish it today anyway.

197
00:17:43,390 --> 00:17:44,180
OK.

198
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
To you,

199
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:53,030
this mural is just
a tiny fraction of your art, right?

200
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,390
Hmm?

201
00:17:56,050 --> 00:17:57,050
I want to

202
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,470
see your art.

203
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:03,100
You've seen it before.

204
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:04,270
Not the mural.

205
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,080
Not stuff you drew in school.

206
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,800
Serious drawings and paintings of yours.

207
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:10,790
Art so spectacular

208
00:18:11,610 --> 00:18:13,260
that warrants you going abroad

209
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,390
and leaving me.

210
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,990
I think I'll be able to
accept your leaving

211
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,710
after seeing them.

212
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,360
So show them to me.

213
00:18:24,660 --> 00:18:25,990
Won't I get to see them

214
00:18:26,370 --> 00:18:28,040
at your art cram school?

215
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:29,990
Let's stop by there today.

216
00:18:30,830 --> 00:18:31,550
What?

217
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:44,290
Woojin didn't

218
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:46,670
get into an accident
in front of the school gate,

219
00:18:46,670 --> 00:18:49,070
but at the entrance
of your art cram school,

220
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,180
when he was on his way

221
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:51,900
to look for you on his bike.

222
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,040
Hey!

223
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:01,570
No.

224
00:19:02,970 --> 00:19:03,970
Why?

225
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:07,250
You don't want to show them to me?

226
00:19:08,140 --> 00:19:09,940
No, that's not what I meant...

227
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:12,750
The art cram school is closed

228
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:13,840
until tomorrow.

229
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:15,720
Yeah?

230
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,440
Yeah.

231
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,900
Then let's go the day after tomorrow.

232
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:20,360
I really want to

233
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:22,010
see your art.

234
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,670
Yeah.

235
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:25,890
OK.

236
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:36,770
He suddenly wants to
go to my art cram school.

237
00:19:36,770 --> 00:19:38,650
Didn't you say he mustn't go there?

238
00:19:38,650 --> 00:19:39,700
Yes, he mustn't.

239
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:41,070
Not even the vicinity.

240
00:19:41,260 --> 00:19:42,120
But I'm busy

241
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:44,290
at home today. I can't be with him.

242
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:45,380
So you should

243
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,930
stay with him for the entire day.

244
00:19:46,930 --> 00:19:47,480
Yeah.

245
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:51,100
I was thinking of
finishing the mural today anyway.

246
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,940
Right, also, um...

247
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,130
Thank you for believing me.

248
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:58,270
Believe what?

249
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:01,130
Uh.

250
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:02,950
Yeah, Eunha.

251
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,150
Yes, believe me.

252
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:06,180
I'll get home safely. Haha.

253
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:07,800
Don't worry.

254
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:08,930
See you at home.

255
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:09,960
OK.

256
00:20:12,210 --> 00:20:13,210
Ha, goodness.

257
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,810
Hey, it's crazy

258
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,920
how my sister still sees me as a kid.

259
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:19,230
Let's go.

260
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:21,100
We have to finish the mural.

261
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:22,860
Yeah, sure.

262
00:21:06,150 --> 00:21:07,150
We're done.

263
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,000
We are.

264
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:12,680
It's really done.

265
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,990
Never thought I'd get to do a mural.

266
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:18,400
I couldn't have done it alone.

267
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,720
I could only finish it thanks to you too.

268
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:36,550
So, you're

269
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:37,790
leaving now?

270
00:21:39,090 --> 00:21:39,780
Hmm?

271
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:43,230
Since the mural's done.

272
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:48,790
Not yet.

273
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,930
Then when?

274
00:21:53,610 --> 00:21:56,270
When should I start
getting mentally prepared?

275
00:21:56,270 --> 00:21:57,270
Don't tell me

276
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:00,360
you're going to
vanish out of the blue again?

277
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:02,820
Just now...

278
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:04,700
To be honest,

279
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,160
I heard everything

280
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:10,550
just now.

281
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,160
He suddenly wants to
go to my art cram school.

282
00:22:17,430 --> 00:22:19,740
Yes, he mustn't.
Not even the vicinity.

283
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:28,210
No, listen...

284
00:22:28,210 --> 00:22:30,390
Why do you never tell me the whole truth?

285
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:31,970
About studying abroad,
you also kept it a secret

286
00:22:31,970 --> 00:22:33,700
and just suddenly informed me.

287
00:22:33,870 --> 00:22:34,980
You say you like me,

288
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:38,200
so why do you keep
taking me for a fool?

289
00:22:38,730 --> 00:22:41,130
-No, it's not like that.
-At the very least,

290
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:45,140
you should give me
a chance to say goodbye.

291
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:48,750
Am I asking too much?

292
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:50,230
Did I ask you not to go?

293
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:52,340
I just...

294
00:22:53,260 --> 00:22:54,770
I just want to see your art,

295
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:56,390
so I can remember you with it.

296
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:59,620
So I can reminisce about you
while looking at your art,

297
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:01,150
and engrave you in my heart.

298
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:10,980
Go.

299
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:13,960
Your study abroad and whatnot.

300
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:16,470
Your feelings;

301
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:18,380
your thoughts...

302
00:23:21,230 --> 00:23:23,390
I can no longer make sense of them.

303
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,320
Actually,

304
00:23:40,020 --> 00:23:42,980
it doesn't matter whether
we have a future or not.

305
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,570
As long as I can keep Woojin safe,

306
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:47,570
as long as I can stop his death,

307
00:23:49,430 --> 00:23:50,970
that's enough, isn't it?

308
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:10,850
[To-Do List: Make sure Lee Woojin
doesn't go to my art cram school.]

309
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,800
Tomorrow is the last day.

310
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,460
Just get through tomorrow safely...

311
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,480
You don't need to know
why I'm doing this.

312
00:24:25,610 --> 00:24:26,610
All I want

313
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:28,880
is to keep you safe.

314
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:42,980
[Art Cram School]

315
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:47,780
[Art Cram School]

316
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,590
Didn't you say he wouldn't come?

317
00:24:53,220 --> 00:24:54,220
Still,

318
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,520
just in case.

319
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,040
Hey!

320
00:25:18,260 --> 00:25:19,180
He's saved.

321
00:25:20,170 --> 00:25:20,900
Really?

322
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:22,900
OMG!

323
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,460
We finally made it.

324
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:29,550
Thank goodness.

325
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:30,660
I know.

326
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:32,290
Let's go.

327
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:42,420
You can tell me now, right?

328
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:44,320
Tell you what?

329
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:45,990
About Woojin's death.

330
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:50,040
You said you'd tell me
how you foresaw everything when it's over.

331
00:25:50,310 --> 00:25:51,050
Well, that's...

332
00:25:51,050 --> 00:25:52,190
Isn't he safe now?

333
00:25:52,210 --> 00:25:53,210
Tell me.

334
00:25:56,340 --> 00:25:58,200
What? Are you not going to tell me?

335
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:04,320
Actually, I'm...

336
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:09,410
from the future.

337
00:26:11,730 --> 00:26:12,570
What?

338
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:14,730
I'm serious.

339
00:26:17,290 --> 00:26:18,590
How did you get here?

340
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:20,370
Through a time machine?

341
00:26:23,140 --> 00:26:24,600
Through this sketchbook.

342
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:30,550
Gosh, you've really got a screw loose.

343
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,360
-Huh?
-You wacko.

344
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:35,760
Hey, I'm s-serious.

345
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:38,560
Oh?

346
00:26:39,250 --> 00:26:39,920
Isn't that

347
00:26:39,980 --> 00:26:40,980
Woojin?

348
00:26:46,570 --> 00:26:47,900
Right. Why is he there?

349
00:26:48,980 --> 00:26:49,440
Oh?

350
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:55,820
Hey, Lee Woojin!

351
00:26:56,470 --> 00:26:57,470
Woojin!

352
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:17,230
[Epilogue]

353
00:27:17,230 --> 00:27:19,180
I don't know why, but your smile

354
00:27:20,730 --> 00:27:23,280
always looked sad to me.

355
00:27:29,310 --> 00:27:31,710
Was it because I sensed
that you'd leave me?

356
00:27:38,070 --> 00:27:39,990
If you were going to leave,

357
00:27:42,150 --> 00:27:44,390
why've you been so nice to me?

358
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:49,860
It's fine.

359
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:53,100
Go.

360
00:27:56,100 --> 00:28:01,780
[Live your own life.
Stay healthy.]

361
00:28:05,710 --> 00:28:06,880
Live your own life.

362
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:09,500
Stay healthy.

363
00:28:14,830 --> 00:28:16,060
Like you,

364
00:28:18,090 --> 00:28:19,970
I'll build my future well too.

365
00:28:23,350 --> 00:28:24,490
By then, I'll...

366
00:28:28,070 --> 00:28:29,370
search for you.

367
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:34,070
We'll meet again.

368
00:29:21,650 --> 00:29:26,320
[Always Meet Again]

